<p><strong>By Stacc Editorial</strong> · We have published 3,500+ SEO articles across 70+ industries and submitted products to dozens of these directories ourselves. · Last updated: April 3, 2026</p>
<p>Most SaaS founders submit their product to 5 directories and stop. That is a mistake that costs months of lost visibility, backlinks, and early users.</p>
<p>Directory submissions are one of the fastest ways to build domain authority for a new product. Each listing creates a backlink, a citation, and a discovery point for potential customers who are actively browsing for tools like yours. The compounding effect is real. Founders who submit to 50+ directories in the first 90 days regularly report jumping from DR 0 to DR 25-35.</p>
<p>We compiled 217 SaaS directories across 12 categories. Every directory on this list is real, active, and accepting submissions as of April 2026. We organized them so you can work through the list in batches of 3-5 per week.</p>
<p><strong>Here is what you will find:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>37 general SaaS and software directories</li>
<li>30 AI tool directories</li>
<li>20 developer and API directories</li>
<li>15 Chrome extension and browser directories</li>
<li>18 open source directories</li>
<li>22 startup launch and discovery platforms</li>
<li>15 review and comparison sites</li>
<li>12 deal and marketplace platforms</li>
<li>12 no-code and automation directories</li>
<li>10 design and landing page directories</li>
<li>14 niche and industry directories</li>
<li>12 investor and funding directories</li>
</ul>
<p>Jump to any category using the table of contents on the left.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="217 SaaS directories organized across 12 categories" src="/images/blog/saas-directories-category-breakdown.webp" /></p>
<h2>General SaaS and Software Directories</h2>
<p>These accept any SaaS product regardless of niche. Start here for maximum coverage and the strongest backlinks.</p>
<p><strong>1. <a href="https://www.producthunt.com/">Product Hunt</a></strong>. The default launch platform for new products. A successful launch day can drive thousands of visitors. Plan your launch for Tuesday-Thursday for the highest engagement.</p>
<p><strong>2. <a href="https://www.g2.com/">G2</a></strong>. The largest B2B software review platform with 5.5 million buyers. Getting reviews here builds massive credibility. Paid and free listing options available.</p>
<p><strong>3. <a href="https://www.capterra.com/">Capterra</a></strong>. Owned by Gartner. One of the highest-authority software directories. Free basic listing with paid boost options. DR 91.</p>
<p><strong>4. <a href="https://www.getapp.com/">GetApp</a></strong>. Sister site to Capterra under Gartner. Separate listing, separate backlink, same submission process. Free to list.</p>
<p><strong>5. <a href="https://www.softwareadvice.com/">Software Advice</a></strong>. Third Gartner property. Submit once through the Gartner Digital Markets portal and get listed across all three.</p>
<p><strong>6. <a href="https://www.saashub.com/">SaaSHub</a></strong>. Independent SaaS marketplace with strong organic traffic. Free submissions accepted. Categorized by alternatives to popular tools.</p>
<p><strong>7. <a href="https://alternativeto.net/">AlternativeTo</a></strong>. People search here when they want to switch from a competitor. High-intent audience. Suggest your product as an alternative to established tools.</p>
<p><strong>8. <a href="https://sourceforge.net/">SourceForge</a></strong>. One of the oldest software directories with 22.5 million monthly visits. Free to list. Strong domain authority for backlinks.</p>
<p><strong>9. <a href="https://clutch.co/">Clutch.co</a></strong>. B2B reviews and comparisons with verified reviews from real clients. Particularly strong for service-based SaaS and agencies.</p>
<p><strong>10. <a href="https://www.goodfirms.co/">GoodFirms</a></strong>. Global directory for software and IT service providers. Free listing with paid premium options for higher visibility.</p>
<p><strong>11. <a href="https://www.softwaresuggest.com/">SoftwareSuggest</a></strong>. Software discovery platform popular in Asia-Pacific markets. Free to list with lead generation features.</p>
<p><strong>12. <a href="https://crozdesk.com/">Crozdesk</a></strong>. SaaS reviews and rankings with a clean comparison interface. Offers a Crozscore quality seal for top-rated products.</p>
<p><strong>13. <a href="https://saasgenius.com/">SaaSGenius</a></strong>. Focused on SaaS comparisons and user reviews. Smaller but growing directory with free submission.</p>
<p><strong>14. <a href="https://www.saasworthy.com/">SaaSworthy</a></strong>. SaaS-only directory offering in-depth analysis and comparison charts. Active community of software buyers.</p>
<p><strong>15. <a href="https://stackshare.io/">StackShare</a></strong>. Tech stack discovery platform with 622K monthly visits. Developers compare and share their tool stacks here. Free to list.</p>
<p><strong>16. <a href="https://www.trustpilot.com/">Trustpilot</a></strong>. Not strictly a SaaS directory, but collecting reviews here boosts trust signals across search results. Free to claim your profile.</p>
<p><strong>17. <a href="https://www.trustradius.com/">TrustRadius</a></strong>. Enterprise-focused review platform. Reviews are detailed and verified, which builds strong buyer confidence.</p>
<p><strong>18. <a href="https://saaspedia.io/">SaaSPedia</a></strong>. Submit your SaaS to 300+ directories through their portal. Also works as a standalone listing.</p>
<p><strong>19. <a href="https://submitsaas.com/">SubmitSaaS</a></strong>. Directory aggregator that helps you submit to 100+ SaaS directories. Also maintains its own searchable directory.</p>
<p><strong>20. <a href="https://saascubes.com/">SaaS Cubes</a></strong>. Curated SaaS directory with editorial reviews and priority listing for new submissions.</p>
<p><strong>21. <a href="https://launchpedia.co/">LaunchPedia</a></strong> ,  150+ directories and platforms indexed in one place. Also serves as its own launch platform for new products.</p>
<p><strong>22. <a href="https://techjury.net/">Techjury</a></strong>. SaaS reviews and insights backed by data. Their tool comparison pages rank well for commercial keywords.</p>
<p><strong>23. <a href="https://softwareselecthq.com/">SoftwareSelect</a></strong>. Clean SaaS discovery interface with category browsing. Free submissions with quick review turnaround.</p>
<p><strong>24. <a href="https://www.platformsdirectory.com/">Platforms Directory</a></strong>. Focused on cross-platform apps and business operation tools. Niche but relevant for B2B products.</p>
<p><strong>25. <a href="https://toolfinder.wiki/">ToolFinder</a></strong>. Browse thousands of tools across categories. Free listing with featured placement options.</p>
<p><strong>26. <a href="https://www.direct2app.com/">Direct2App</a></strong>. Matches businesses with SaaS and AI tools. Free submission with category-based browsing.</p>
<p><strong>27. <a href="https://www.b2bstack.com.br/">B2B Stack</a></strong>. Largest B2B SaaS directory in Latin America. Essential if you serve Portuguese or Spanish-speaking markets.</p>
<p><strong>28. <a href="https://saasdatabase.net/">SaaS Database</a></strong>. Comprehensive listing of SaaS companies organized by industry, size, and technology stack.</p>
<p><strong>29. <a href="https://confettisaas.com/">ConfettiSaaS</a></strong>. Indie-focused SaaS discovery platform. Free submission with playful branding that attracts early adopters.</p>
<p><strong>30. <a href="https://opensaas.directory/">Open SaaS Directory</a></strong>. Open source and self-hosted SaaS alternatives. If your product is open source or has a self-hosted option, list it here.</p>
<p><strong>31. <a href="https://webspot.app/">Webspot</a></strong>. Curated directory of the best websites and tools on the internet. Editorial selection process.</p>
<p><strong>32. <a href="https://uno.directory/">Uno Directory</a></strong>. Curated directory across all tool categories. Free dofollow backlink with submission.</p>
<p><strong>33. <a href="https://nachonacho.com/">NachoNacho</a></strong>. B2B SaaS marketplace where businesses discover, buy, and manage software subscriptions.</p>
<p><strong>34. <a href="https://tooldirs.com/">ToolDirs</a></strong>. General tools directory with category filtering. Quick approval process for new submissions.</p>
<p><strong>35. <a href="https://deeplaunch.io/">Deeplaunch</a></strong>. Online tools directory with featured listing options and strong organic visibility.</p>
<p><strong>36. <a href="https://www.thankjohn.com/">Thank John</a></strong>. Free tool submissions with featured placement. Simple submission form with fast review.</p>
<p><strong>37. <a href="https://dofollow.tools/">Dofollow.Tools</a></strong>. Submit your tool and get a dofollow backlink. Straightforward value proposition for link builders.</p>
