<p><strong>85. <a href="https://console.dev/">Console.dev</a></strong>. Developer tool reviews with a weekly newsletter. Getting featured drives sustained developer traffic.</p>
<p><strong>86. <a href="https://toolsforcreators.com/">ToolsForCreators</a></strong>. Tools directory for developers and creators. Category-based browsing with free submissions.</p>
<p><strong>87. <a href="https://free-for.dev/">Free for Dev</a></strong>. Massive list of SaaS, PaaS, and IaaS offerings that have free tiers for developers. If your product has a free tier, this list is essential.</p>
<h2>Chrome Extension and Browser Directories</h2>
<p>Beyond the Chrome Web Store, these directories help browser extension makers gain visibility and backlinks.</p>
<p><strong>88. <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/">Chrome Web Store</a></strong>. The primary distribution channel. Every Chrome extension must be here. Optimize your listing title, description, and screenshots.</p>
<p><strong>89. <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/">Firefox Add-ons</a></strong>. Mozilla's official extension store. Port your Chrome extension to Firefox and list it here for a second distribution channel.</p>
<p><strong>90. <a href="https://microsoftedge.microsoft.com/addons/">Microsoft Edge Add-ons</a></strong>. Edge's extension marketplace. Chromium-based, so most Chrome extensions work with minimal changes.</p>
<p><strong>91. <a href="https://launchdirectories.com/directory-submission/chrome-extension">Chrome Extension Directories (LaunchDirectories)</a></strong>. Submission service for Chrome extensions across 100+ directories. Saves time on manual submissions.</p>
<p><strong>92. <a href="https://webstoreextensions.com/">Webstore Extensions</a></strong>. Independent marketplace for browser extensions across Chrome, Firefox, Edge, and Brave. Free to submit.</p>
<p><strong>93. <a href="https://extensionboss.com/">ExtensionBoss</a></strong>. Directory of browser extensions with user ratings and reviews. Free listing available.</p>
<p><strong>94. <a href="https://extension.dev/">Extension.dev</a></strong>. Developer-focused browser extension directory. Good for technical extensions targeting developers.</p>
<p><strong>95. <a href="https://browserextension.dev/">BrowserExtension.dev</a></strong>. Curated list of useful browser extensions organized by category. Submit your extension for editorial review.</p>
<p><strong>96. <a href="https://chrome-stats.com/">ChromeStats</a></strong>. Chrome extension analytics and directory. Tracks installs, ratings, and market trends for extensions.</p>
<p><strong>97. <a href="https://extpose.com/">ExtPose</a></strong>. Chrome Web Store analytics platform. Also functions as a discovery directory for popular extensions.</p>
<p><strong>98. <a href="https://www.crx4chrome.com/">Crx4Chrome</a></strong>. Alternative Chrome extension download directory. Provides visibility outside the official Web Store.</p>
<p><strong>99. <a href="https://alternativeto.net/category/browsers/browser-extensions/">AlternativeTo (Browser Extensions)</a></strong>. Browser extension category on AlternativeTo. Submit your extension as an alternative to popular ones.</p>
<p><strong>100. <a href="https://extensionworkshop.com/">Firefox Extension Workshop</a></strong>. Mozilla's official resource for extension developers. Lists extensions and provides development documentation.</p>
<p><strong>101. <a href="https://www.producthunt.com/topics/chrome-extensions">ProductHunt (Chrome Extensions)</a></strong>. Product Hunt has a dedicated Chrome extensions topic. Launch your extension here for focused attention.</p>
<p><strong>102. <a href="https://indieextensions.com/">IndieExtensions</a></strong>. Directory for indie-built browser extensions. Small but targeted community of extension enthusiasts.</p>
